{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S6 1ba5: Docs slice)]\n\nAudited this Docs child's contribution to the parent acceptance/success criteria; every absence cross-checked against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 6d56 materialize core, S2 70c7 cache+janitor, S3 fa49 gate threading, S4 30b3 attested signing, S5 b7fa CLI/MCP schema surfacing). This child is the documentation slice; the union of children covers every parent criterion. EMPTY G3 findings list.\n\n4-bucket coverage map (parent AC -> covering child/children; this docs child's role):\n- AC1 (no attested gate reads working tree; all read faithful snapshot at pinned SHA) — FULLY covered by S1+S3. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child (Scope: \"Out: code (S1-S5)\"). Not an absence.\n- AC2 (signed verdict records verified_at_sha + reproducible) — FULLY covered by S4 (AC1) atop S1's immutable SHA. This child DOCUMENTS the signing/verified_at_sha semantics (its AC3) + in-toto Statement shape (its AC4). Behavior owned by S4; docs half here. Not an absence.\n- AC3 (local reads in-place checkout AND cannot sign) — covered by S3 (in-place read) + S4 (signing bar). This child DOCUMENTS attested-signs/local-never-signs + fail-closed-vs-local-still-runs (its AC2/AC3). Not an absence.\n- AC4 (concurrent gates, no lock contention/corruption; atomic population; delete-on-last-close) — FULLY covered by S1+S2. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child. Not an absence.\n- AC5 (cache+janitor reclaim under pressure) — behavior FULLY covered by S2. This child DOCUMENTS disk-cap behavior (its AC5). Not an absence.\n- AC6 (private-repo fetch failure surfaces descriptive actionable credential error) — SPLIT: S1 (AC5) RAISES the error; THIS child is the DOCS PRIMARY OWNER (its AC1: README MCP-setup + docs/jira-sync-setup.md state the requirement + how to supply, grep-able; its AC2: message+remedy + fail-closed/local-still-runs in a named file). The \"actionable\" facet (how to supply credentials) is precisely this child's contribution. Clean split.\n- AC7 (portable: no external tar; no hardcoded /tmp; flock+mkdir fallback) — implementation FULLY covered by S1; this child DOCUMENTS REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + EFS/NFS flock caveat (its AC5, xref alto-fruit-punch). Clean split.\n- AC8 (all six children closed; make lint + full suite green) — STRUCTURAL/meta epic-completion; covered by existence of all six children (this is #6 of 6) + each child's green-bar obligation. Not an absence.\n\nNamed-consumer hand-offs landing on this child (covered-by-named-consumer, not absences):\n- S4 (30b3) \"What\" explicitly delegates its HMAC-trust-model docs to S6 (\"its limits ... are DOCUMENTED in S6\") — claimed by this child's AC4.\n- S1 (6d56) defers the descriptive credential MESSAGE detail to S6 — claimed by this child's AC2.\n- S5 (b7fa) scopes prose docs out (\"Out: prose docs (S6)\"); ref/source PROSE claimed here by AC3 (schema-text vs prose split clean).\n\nSuccess-criteria narrative decomposes onto AC1-AC3/AC6; this child carries the operator/trust-model documentation surface the snapshot model newly requires (fetch-credential prerequisite, descriptive failure, attested/local + origin/main + verified_at_sha semantics, HMAC limits + in-toto shape, REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR/disk-cap/EFS-flock). Introduces no uncovered obligation.\n\nNote (scope, not a G3 finding): the standing G4 dependency-gap on S4 (30b3) about routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into attest.py is a code consistency seam between S3/S4, unrelated to this docs child; it leaves no parent criterion unclaimed.\n\nConclusion: this child cleanly covers the documentation slice; no parent acceptance/success criterion is left uncovered by the roster. No G3 finding for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782526632627910001,"uuid":"8badf2ac-9fa4-40af-a216-69d02c4d32ff"}